{"title_page": "John Charles Harding, 2nd Baron Harding of Petherton", "text_new": "'''John Charles Harding, 2nd Baron Harding of Petherton''' (12 February 1928 &ndash; 6 June 2016) was a [[British Army]] officer and [[hereditary peer]].\n\nHarding was educated at [[Marlborough College]] and [[Worcester College, Oxford]] (MA). He was commissioned into the [[British Army]] and served with the [[11th Hussars]], reaching the rank of [[major]]. He succeeded his father [[John Harding, 1st Baron Harding of Petherton]] to the title of [[Baron Harding of Petherton]] in 1989.\n\nBy his wife, Harriet, daughter of [[Major General]] Francis Hare (whom he married in 1966), he has two sons and one daughter. Harriet died on 4 December 2012. His daughter, [[Dido Harding|Dido Harding, Baroness Harding of Winscombe]], is married to Conservative MP [[John Penrose]]. Harding died in June 2016 at the age of 88.<ref>http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/204458/harding</ref>\n\n==Arms==\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|image=[[File:Coronet of a British Baron.svg|centre|150px]][[File:Harding of Petherton Escutcheon.png|centre|200px]]\n|escutcheon = Argent on a bend Azure between two lions passant guardant Gules as many kukris in saltire Proper between two martlets Or.\n|crest = Out of a mural crown Gules a cubit arm in armour the hand gauntleted grasping a field marshal's baton in bend sinister Proper.\n|supporters = Dexter a private of the [[1st Life Guards]] of early nineteenth century; sinister a [[Somerset Light Infantry]]man of the late eighteenth century; both habited and accoutred Proper.\n|motto = Vigilant & Resolute <ref>{{cite book|title=Debrett's Peerage |date=1973}}</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[http://www.burkespeerage.com/FamilyHomepage.aspx?FID=6137 Harding of Petherton]. ''[[Burke's Peerage]]''\n\n==External links==\n*{{Hansard-contribs | mr-john-harding | Lord Harding of Petherton }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[John Harding, 1st Baron Harding of Petherton|Allan Francis John Harding]]}}\n{{s-ttl\n | title  = [[Baron Harding of Petherton]]\n | years  = 1989\u20132016\n}}\n{{s-aft| after=William Harding}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Harding, John Charles}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:People educated at Marlborough College]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Worcester College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Barons in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:11th Hussars officers]]\n[[Category:John Harding family]]\n{{UK-mil-bio-stub}}\n{{UK-baron-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''John Charles Harding, 2nd Baron Harding of Petherton''' (12 February 1928 &ndash; 6 June 2016) was a [[British Army]] officer and [[hereditary peer]].\n\nHarding was educated at [[Marlborough College]] and [[Worcester College, Oxford]] (MA). He was commissioned into the [[British Army]] and served with the [[11th Hussars]] reaching the rank of [[Major]]. He succeeded his father [[John Harding, 1st Baron Harding of Petherton]] to the title of [[Baron Harding of Petherton]] in 1989.\n\nBy his wife, Harriet, daughter of [[Major-General]] Francis Hare [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (whom he married in 1966), he has two sons and one daughter. Harriet died on 4 December 2012. His daughter [[Dido Harding]] (Baroness Harding of Winscombe) is married to Conservative MP [[John Penrose]]. Harding died in June 2016 at the age of 88.<ref>http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/204458/harding</ref>\n\n==Arms==\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|image=[[File:Coronet of a British Baron.svg|centre|150px]][[File:Harding of Petherton Escutcheon.png|centre|200px]]\n|escutcheon = Argent on a bend Azure between two lions passant guardant Gules as many kukris in saltire Proper between two martlets Or.\n|crest = Out of a mural crown Gules a cubit arm in armour the hand gauntleted grasping a field marshal's baton in bend sinister Proper.\n|supporters = Dexter a private of the [[1st Life Guards]] of early nineteenth century; sinister a [[Somerset Light Infantry]]man of the late eighteenth century; both habited and accoutred Proper.\n|motto = Vigilant & Resolute <ref>{{cite book|title=Debrett's Peerage |date=1973}}</ref>}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n*[http://www.burkespeerage.com/FamilyHomepage.aspx?FID=6137 Harding of Petherton]. ''[[Burke's Peerage]]''\n\n==External links==\n*{{Hansard-contribs | mr-john-harding | Lord Harding of Petherton }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[John Harding, 1st Baron Harding of Petherton|Allan Francis John Harding]]}}\n{{s-ttl\n | title  = [[Baron Harding of Petherton]]\n | years  = 1989\u20132016\n}}\n{{s-aft| after=William Harding}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Harding, John Charles}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:People educated at Marlborough College]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Worcester College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Barons in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:11th Hussars officers]]\n[[Category:John Harding family]]\n{{UK-mil-bio-stub}}\n{{UK-baron-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Abraham, B.S.", "label": "safe", "comment": "tweaks/corrections/tidy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Charles_Harding,_2nd_Baron_Harding_of_Petherton"}
